Rating: 4
I was looking for a good lobster roll recipe and came across this one...it was fantastic and super super easy!!! I halved the recipe, using only lobster (steamed tails for 8 minutes) and substituted fennel greens for the dill as that's what I had on hand. Served open-faced on a toasted Hawaiian Roll Hamburger Bun.

Rating: 4
Yum! Served on toasted Hawaiian rolls with center pulled out. I agree the mix is so good so you don't need the whole roll. I got great reviews at my Golde Globes party.

Rating: 4
I served these at a graduation party along with other appetizers and people loved them! They were the first to go. I did cut out the bread in the middle of the rolls because you couldn't taste enough of the lobster. I would recommend serving the lobster with crackers next time. Overall, it was delicious and a big hit with guests.

Rating: 4
I served this recipe as part of a cocktail party with several appetizers. Rather than putting the salad in the roll I served it along side pre-sliced rolls so that people could make their own little sandwich. It seemed like once they were assembled it would be more difficult to save any leftovers. There were also crackers on the table. Most people put the salad on a cracker rather than in the roll. In the future, I think I will just serve it with crackers instead. Or maybe even on an endive leaf. The flavor of the salad on its own is too good it cover with a lot of bread.

Rating: 4
These were wonderful! I served them on crostini for a dinner party and everyone loved them. Great, light, lemony flavor that let the delicate flavors of the seafood come through. Definitely a keeper!

